  "prompt": "How is the word 'intimation' used in a sentence?",
  "response": "The word \"intimation\" refers to a subtle or indirect hint or suggestion. Here are a few examples of how it can be used in a sentence:\n\n1. She gave no intimation that she was leaving the company until she handed in her resignation letter.\n2. His stern expression was an intimation that the conversation was over.\n3. The sudden drop in temperature was an intimation of the approaching storm.\n4. Despite her calm demeanor, there was an intimation of worry in her eyes.\n5. The novel's title is an intimation of the dark themes explored in its pages.",
